HEADWORD: Overhip
<hw>O`ver*hip"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overhipped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overhipping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[<ets>Over</ets> + a
word akin to E. <ets>hop</ets> to skip.]</ety> <def>To pass over by, or
as by a hop; to skip over; hence, to overpass.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧When the time is <xex>overhipt</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
